(1586, 289, '_presto_callout_header', 'field_5b0db43854cb0'),
(1587, 289, 'presto_callout_content', 'With data volumes and types of data increasing on a daily basis, placing this data on a flexible storage medium such as HDFS or a cloud object storage such as Amazon''s S3, S3-compatible stores (Minio, ceph), and Azure''s Blob Storage provides a company with great flexibility on when and where they consume this data. Architected for separation of storage and compute, Presto can <strong>scale up and down</strong> based on your analytics demand to access this data. There’s no need to move your data and provisioning compute to the exact need results in <strong>significant cost savings.</strong>'),
