(10010, 411, 'page_blocks_0_block_content', 'Presto was originally developed by Facebook to scale to the data size and performance they needed. In Fall 2012 a small team of four engineers at Facebook started working on Presto. By Spring 2013, the first version was successfully rolled out within Facebook. Later that year, Facebook open sourced Presto under the <u><a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache License</a></u>. Since then the Presto community has thrived with a lot of contributions from other companies such as Starburst, Teradata, Netflix, Airbnb, LinkedIn, and Uber.'),
