(10561, 419, 'page_blocks_0_block_content', 'Presto can be used in many different platforms and locations. From public cloud to on-premises, it is truly platform agnostic. Companies use Presto for single reporting applications to a single enterprise-wide query engine. The tremendous growth cloud computing and <u><a href="https://www.gartner.com/it-glossary/self-service-business-intelligence">self-service BI</a></u> demand a more agile approach to data access by data consumers.\r\n\r\nAllowing data to be consumed by anyone that needs access has become increasingly important in any organization as well as “data latency”. Data latency is the time it takes to make the data available to data consumers. This metric has become critical to the success of many departments whether they are looking at IoT data to providing customers with important buying decision data.\r\n\r\nPresto provides an easy way to allow access to data in a variety of sources using industry standard SQL query language. End users don’t have to learn any new complex language or some new tool, they can use whatever existing tools they have been using and are comfortable with.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-418" src="http://starburstdata.dev.cc/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/starburst-data-sources-analyst-tools-diagram.jpg" alt="" width="1921" height="634" />'),
