(12458, 497, 'blog_external_excerpt', 'It seems like ancient history now, but “big data” was once a hot field with startups, investors, and big companies all buzzing with hype. Then the tech industry moved on, and marketers crowned data science and machine learning the Next Big Things (at least until blockchain takes over).\r\nOf course, big data never really went away—though many companies did. In fact, there’s a lot happening in the field, and some of it is linked to the rise of machine learning and artificial intelligence applications. If you’re looking for a guide to what has happened—and what the future holds—you could do worse than talk to a guy named Justin Borgman (pictured).'),
