(12716, 508, 'page_blocks_3_block_content', 'Deploy Presto on premises co-located on your Hadoop cluster or its own standalone cluster. If Presto is deployed co-located on the Hadoop cluster, it must be the only compute engine running. For example, Spark and Presto complement each other in the data pipeline, but should not be run at the same time. Additionally connect Presto to your on premises object store such as Minio, Ceph, Cloudian, or OpenIO.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-408" src="http://starburstdata.dev.cc/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/starburst-reference-architecture-on-premises.jpg" alt="" width="1921" height="1066" />'),
